node.title: Victoria records 1,343 new local COVID-19 cases and 10 deaths as border with NSW reopens
node.description: There are now 18,952 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 345 people have died during the current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,343\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and 10\u00a0deaths as the state's border with New South Wales reopens.", "There are now 18,952\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 345\u00a0people have died during the current Delta outbreak.", "There are 634\u00a0people in hospital in Victoria with COVID-19, of whom 109\u00a0are in intensive care, and 73\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The new cases were detected from 66,155\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 14,255\u00a0doses of vaccine given at state-run centres yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "The new cases come as Victoria opens its border to New South Wales for the first time in months.", "More to come.", "", "
